10/11/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- NATO Secretary-General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer will pay a visit to Bucharest on November 16th, the Romanian foreign ministry said Thursday (November 9th). Scheffer will meet with President Traian Basescu, Foreign Minister Mihai-Razvan Ungureanu and Defence Minister Sorin Frunzaverde. Talks are expected to focus on the Romanian contribution to the achievement of NATO goals, participation in peacekeeping missions, issues in the Western Balkans, the situation in Afghanistan, and the upcoming NATO summit in Riga. 
Also Thursday, the Standing Offices of the Chamber of Deputies and the senate adopted a decision stipulating that Romanian Members of European Parliament (MEPs) will be allowed to temporarily retain their seats in the Romanian parliament after the country joins the EU. By November 28th, parliamentary parties must submit a list of MEPs and possible modifications to the members of their delegations. (Rompres, Mediafax - 09/11/06)
